# Target Dash: Privacy Policy
This privacy policy governs your use of the software application Target Dash (“Application”) for mobile devices that was created by Project Everything. The Application is a game that requires the user to match the colour of circular objects that drop from above with the colour presented in the form of a 4-coloured target on the screen, the goal is to reach a higher score than previously achieved. The Application does not offer any paid content and attempts a simplistic approach to overall functionality.

+ 1. Data Collection

The Application does not collect any personal or precise real-time information from users, we do not require you to provide any login, financial, geolocation based or private information when using our app, we don’t collect, share or use any sensitive information about you or your device. 

+ 2. User Provided Information

The Application requires the user to enter a “nickname” into a text-entry field for the purposes of registering a player score for the Leaderboard function, the data is not stored internally or used in any manner by us other than for the purpose of displaying a username next to the scores achieved in-game, the function cannot be used with an empty text-field. Users are not asked for a login or password and can change the nickname at any point in time.

+ 3. Third Party Access

We do not collect or transmit user data to external services, but may still be required to disclose User Provided information in situations such as:

If required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process.
If Project Everything is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of its assets; we will ensure a notice on our relevant platforms of any change in ownership or uses of this information.

+ 4. Age Limit & Children

Upon registering a nickname for the Application, you represent that you are at least 13 years of age. However, we do not know the specific age of individual users of our Application. If you are under 13 years of age, please do not provide your personal data (using your real name in the nickname section) to us or use the Application to make your personal data available to others.

If we discover that we hold personal data relating to a user under 13 years of age, we will take appropriate measures to ensure that we process that data according to the requirements of applicable laws and regulations, or promptly delete the data. 

We do not use the Application to knowingly solicit data from or market to children under the age of 13. If a parent or guardian becomes aware that his or her child has provided us with information without their consent, he or she should contact us at projecteverythingbiz@gmail.com. We will do a thorough investigation; if this is correct, we will delete such information from the Application within a reasonable time. If you are a parent/guardian and have any concerns regarding your child's potential use of the Application and our policies on data collection or user provided information, you may refer to both the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) of 1998 and the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) of 2018 for more information.

If you have reason to believe we hold personal data relating to a user under 13 years of age, please contact us.

+ 5. In-Game Advertisements

This Application features selective Interstitial and Banner type advertisements of external products and/or services between the intended target audience, in accordance with Google Play approved Ad services, these advertisements do not use your data for commercial purposes, and are chosen based on the intended market range of the Application. We are not directly affiliated with the products or services displayed within these advertisements. 

+ 6. Policy Updates

This Privacy Policy may be updated in the future for any reason. We will make the necessary announcements on our platforms about changes and adhere to the guidelines set forth by the Application’s publishing services during any potential update. You are advised to regularly consult this Privacy Policy for any changes.
 
+ 7. Contact

If you have any questions regarding privacy while using the Application, or have questions about our practices, please contact us via email at projecteverythingbiz@gmail.com. 
